{
  "stem": "3100.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I remember those times, I used to joke around later that the only little-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] little of-- of-- of-- comfort that I got is when I was itching and I could scratch myself.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then not yet.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then I was throughout the end of '41.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then in 1942, in the beginning of 1942, I kept on-- had a steady place of work for-- I worked for the Kommandantur.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had already a certificate that I'm working for them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, in March of 1942, we received a message through a Polack that my oldest brother, Chaim Yisroel, was taken out that night from his home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His wife and two children were left, and he was taken to Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, we didn't know where he was taken.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But later on, I found out that he was taken to Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, the Passover approached.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was very hard, and we managed to scramble through to have some kind of a few matzahs in the house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remembered that the Seder of my-- with my parents when I saw them the last time and the rest of my sisters and brother that we were together was on Passover, 1942.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then three days later, and to be exact, on April the 12th-- I'll never forget this date, 1942.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a Sunday, three days after Pesach.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Around 12 o'clock, the entire city was circled around with police, [NON-ENGLISH], SS soldiers, and Polish police, too-- with dogs and with loud speakers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they called upon all the Jewish people must leave their homes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They told us that we must be resettled [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and because it's a law of the German government.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
